msgid "not ready for prime time"
msgstr "not ready for prime time"

#: ../../N/not-ready-for-prime-time.rst:7
msgid "adj\\."
msgstr "形容詞"

#: ../../N/not-ready-for-prime-time.rst:9
msgid ""
"Usable, but only just so; not very robust; for internal use only. Said of a "
"program or device. Often connotes that the thing will be made more solid "
":ref:`Real-Soon-Now`\\. This term comes from the ensemble name of the "
"original cast of *Saturday Night Live*\\, the \"Not Ready for Prime Time "
"Players\". It has extra flavor for hackers because of the special (though "
"now semi-obsolescent) meaning of :ref:`prime-time`\\. Compare :ref:`beta`\\."
msgstr ""
"使えるが、かろうじてそうであるにすぎない。あまり堅牢でない。内部使用のみ。プログラムやデバイスについて言う。しばしばそのものが\\ "
":ref:`Real-Soon-Now`\\ により堅固になることを含意する。この語は\\ *Saturday Night Live*\\ "
"の元のキャストのアンサンブル名「Not Ready for Prime Time Players」に由来する。\\ :ref:`prime-"
"time`\\ の特別な(今では半ば廃れた)意味のため、ハッカーにとっては余分な風味がある。\\ :ref:`beta`\\ と比較せよ。"
